|CKBLeaving the Street Samurai|000

|CK0Leaving removes the Street Samurai contract, command soul, Guild Level and
Cortex progression access, Edge and Heat, guild strain contribution, firmware
authentication, active guild effects, maintenance automation, clinic coverage,
private network membership, and all installed Street Samurai signature
cyberware.|000

|CKBWhat remains|000
|CK0Every installed Street Samurai signature implant is permanently
decommissioned and destroyed when membership ends. It is not extracted into
inventory, dropped, refunded, or converted into salvage.|000

|CK0Unrelated cyberware remains installed. Uninstalled hardware carried in
inventory also remains yours. Only installed implants identified as Street
Samurai signature hardware are destroyed.|000

|CKBAfter leaving|000
|CK0Former members can use an ordinary staffed ripperdoc for unrelated
cyberware. Rin's contract-covered service and the private Cortex network
require active membership. Rejoining uses the normal enrollment procedure and
installs a fresh intake Cortex OS; previously installed signature implants do
not survive the severed contract.|000

|CKBInactive is different|000
|CK0An inactive contract preserves membership and usually clears after
conflicting equipment is removed. Do not leave merely to solve an inactive
state. Check samstatus, remove the conflicting gear, and review samhelp
contract first.|000

|YKBLeaving permanently destroys every installed Street Samurai signature
implant. Review your loadout before severing the contract.|000
